{
  "_comment": "Spec-derived manifest (cliwright GOAL.md §0/§11). The FULL Web API method set is enumerated from Slack's own docs index JSON (see api_method_source), not model recall. Verbs map 1:1 to Web API methods except the marked client-side composites. scripts/spec-check.sh enforces surface⊆manifest (consistency); scripts/spec-completeness.sh enforces manifest≈full-API (completeness). The Web API is RPC-method-oriented, not CRUD — verbs are the API's own actions (see DECISIONS.md). The surface is deliberately scoped to Slack-MCP parity + Socket Mode listen per the commissioning brief; the shortfall vs the 308-method enumeration is recorded as a coverage-waiver in DECISIONS.md (admin.* is Enterprise-Grid-only: 106 of the 308).",
  "binary": "slackctl",
  "base_url": "https://slack.com/api",
  "auth": "bearer token (xoxb bot / xoxp user; xapp app-level for Socket Mode)",
